xt-block ssrcss-17u89h5-TextWrapper e1ekt5r40"><h2>Defrosting</h2><p>Defros=
t your meat in the fridge or in a cool room below 10=E2=80=9315C rather tha=
n at room temperature, so that the outside remains cold. It is particularly=
 important to ensure that poultry is fully defrosted before cooking. Defros=
t turkey in a cool room for 3=E2=80=934 hours per kilogram or in a fridge a=
t 4C for 10=E2=80=9312 hours per kilogram.</p></div></div></div></div><div =
data-layout=3D"single" class=3D"ssrcss-1myx8lm-Row enh46940"><div><div><div=
 data-component=3D"text-block" class=3D"text-block ssrcss-17u89h5-TextWrapp=
er e1ekt5r40"><h2>Resting meat</h2><p>Once your meat is cooked, rest it in =
a warm place covered with tented foil for the time specified in the calcula=
tor. During this time it will become more juicy and easier to carve.</p><p>=
